1
00:00:07,033 --> 00:00:11,233
笙ｪI've braved the storms, walked through the rain笙ｪ

2
00:00:11,267 --> 00:00:14,633
笙ｪSeen the highs and lows along the way笙ｪ

3
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:18,033
笙ｪBut you stay quiet, never change笙ｪ

4
00:00:18,233 --> 00:00:21,633
笙ｪLike a child who dreams beneath the stars笙ｪ

5
00:00:21,700 --> 00:00:25,033
笙ｪI've read the story in your eyes笙ｪ

6
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:28,533
笙ｪAnd finally, nothing's left to hide笙ｪ

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:32,133
笙ｪYou won't give in to a world so cold笙ｪ

8
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:35,733
笙ｪSo you wander through it on your own笙ｪ

9
00:00:35,867 --> 00:00:39,333
笙ｪMaybe fate has drawn us near笙ｪ

10
00:00:39,433 --> 00:00:42,333
笙ｪJust to help you learn to believe笙ｪ

11
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:45,500
笙ｪEverything you've questioned deep inside笙ｪ

12
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:49,733
笙ｪI'll be the proof you need笙ｪ

13
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:51,167
笙ｪI've made my choice笙ｪ

14
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:54,133
笙ｪFor you, I'll be brave and break the rules笙ｪ

15
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,367
笙ｪWhat's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?笙ｪ

16
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,933
笙ｪOne day, all of this will turn into memories笙ｪ

17
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:04,367
笙ｪEvery storm we faced will turn into our life's scenery笙ｪ

18
00:01:05,133 --> 00:01:08,033
笙ｪFor you, I'll be brave and break the rules笙ｪ

19
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:11,267
笙ｪWhat's there to fear even if the world is right and I am wrong?笙ｪ

20
00:01:11,967 --> 00:01:14,833
笙ｪEven if, in the end, the whole world turns against me笙ｪ

21
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:18,267
笙ｪI won't regret having loved you笙ｪ

22
00:01:18,367 --> 00:01:21,933
笙ｪWith all my heart笙ｪ

23
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:25,767
笙ｪI've held you close笙ｪ

24
00:01:25,867 --> 00:01:29,467
笙ｪWalked by your side笙ｪ

25
00:01:29,633 --> 00:01:33,933
笙ｪAnd loved the fire that burned inside you笙ｪ

26
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,467
[The First Frost]

27
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:36,967
[Adapted from the novel of the same name by Zhu Yi on www.jjwxc.net]

28
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,333
See you, Dad.

29
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,467
If there is anything you don't know, just ask.

30
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:53,867
- Okay! - You bag.

31
00:01:56,200 --> 00:01:56,767
Bye.

32
00:01:56,767 --> 00:01:57,433
Bye.

33
00:01:58,633 --> 00:02:00,367
It's Class 17.

34
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:01,567
- Okay! - Make sure you go to the right class.

35
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:04,167
Remember to drink water. Hot water.

36
00:02:19,867 --> 00:02:20,567
Senior.

37
00:02:20,667 --> 00:02:22,467
Can you please tell me where Class 17 Year 10 is?

38
00:02:22,967 --> 00:02:24,367
Sorry, I just started school here.

39
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:27,400
Go downstairs, turn left, and enter the building.

40
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:31,267
And?

41
00:02:32,133 --> 00:02:32,867
And?

42
00:02:33,700 --> 00:02:35,467
And check the classroom number on the door yourself.

43
00:02:35,900 --> 00:02:37,067
Or do you expect me, your senior

44
00:02:37,067 --> 00:02:38,567
to read them out one by one for you?

45
00:02:40,433 --> 00:02:41,533
My junior.

46
00:02:43,033 --> 00:02:43,967
Thank you, Senior.

47
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:50,267
Sorry.

48
00:03:02,867 --> 00:03:03,467
Excuse me!

49
00:03:06,600 --> 00:03:07,300
Sang Yan?

50
00:03:07,667 --> 00:03:08,633
I'm Wen Yifan.

51
00:03:10,233 --> 00:03:11,033
Oh, Wen Yifan.

52
00:03:13,367 --> 00:03:15,167
Everyone on the list showed up except you and Sang Yan.

53
00:03:15,300 --> 00:03:16,033
Sorry.

54
00:03:16,033 --> 00:03:17,833
Sang Yan sounds like a girl's name

55
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:18,833
so I thought you were Sang Yan.

56
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:21,400
Excuse me.

57
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:23,833
Sorry, sir.

58
00:03:23,967 --> 00:03:24,633
I came late.

59
00:03:24,633 --> 00:03:25,300
It's him?

60
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,067
Late on your first day?

61
00:03:28,367 --> 00:03:29,467
Did you two come together?

62
00:03:29,700 --> 00:03:30,933
No, we didn't.

63
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:32,500
I just couldn't find my way

64
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,233
and it took a while.

65
00:03:33,900 --> 00:03:35,567
What about you? What's your excuse?

66
00:03:38,567 --> 00:03:40,067
My dad didn't know I was in high school now

67
00:03:40,367 --> 00:03:41,400
and sent me to junior high school.

68
00:03:45,467 --> 00:03:46,167
Are you going in

69
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:47,900
Miss Sang Yan?

70
00:03:48,767 --> 00:03:50,067
I, the senior, would like you to go in first

71
00:03:51,367 --> 00:03:52,600
my junior from middle school.

72
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,600
Take those two seats at the back.

73
00:04:02,767 --> 00:04:03,400
Go.

74
00:04:07,033 --> 00:04:07,800
That was

75
00:04:08,233 --> 00:04:09,667
the first time I saw him.

76
00:04:12,067 --> 00:04:13,067
When the teacher got our names wrong

77
00:04:13,767 --> 00:04:14,867
I found myself momentarily lost

78
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:16,300
forgetting that he was Sang Yan

79
00:04:18,433 --> 00:04:19,267
and I was

80
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:20,767
Wen Yifan.

81
00:04:25,233 --> 00:04:26,133
For a moment

82
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,167
it was like there was suddenly

83
00:04:29,133 --> 00:04:30,933
another me in this world.

84
00:04:39,367 --> 00:04:44,767
[Episode 2]
[Your Name]

85
00:04:52,167 --> 00:04:56,333
[Eight years later]

86
00:05:00,267 --> 00:05:01,133
Dian.

87
00:05:02,867 --> 00:05:03,500
Qiao

88
00:05:03,500 --> 00:05:04,400
all done with your work?

89
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:04,900
Yep.

90
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:05,433
Let's go.

91
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:06,500
We'll party more later!

92
00:05:07,033 --> 00:05:08,433
You've been standing all night. Aren't you tired?

93
00:05:08,667 --> 00:05:10,867
It's been ages since we had a gathering like this.

94
00:05:10,867 --> 00:05:12,200
Surely we can't call it a night just yet.

95
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:13,267
Let's go!

96
00:05:13,267 --> 00:05:14,233
But I still have to go back

97
00:05:14,233 --> 00:05:15,133
and organize my materials tonight.

98
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:17,933
Then I'll wait for you to finish organizing your materials.

99
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:21,300
I heard there's a New Year's event at Overtime tonight.

100
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,167
I'm already worn out from working overtime

101
00:05:25,167 --> 00:05:26,033
and now I have to go to Overtime?

102
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:27,267
I'm definitely not going.

103
00:05:27,433 --> 00:05:29,267
No way, you have to come with me.

104
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,167
Yes way.

105
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:31,433
Please come with me.

106
00:05:31,433 --> 00:05:32,333
- All right now. - I'll wait for you.

107
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:32,933
Be good

108
00:05:32,933 --> 00:05:33,500
and go by yourself.

109
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:34,867
- I can wait for you. - Come on.

110
00:05:34,867 --> 00:05:36,133
Just go. Don't wait for me.

111
00:05:37,033 --> 00:05:37,933
- Bye. - Stay safe.

112
00:05:37,933 --> 00:05:38,933
Got it.

113
00:05:39,767 --> 00:05:41,167
Why didn't you go hang out with your friend?

114
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:45,800
Come here.

115
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:54,433
Madam.

116
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:58,933
We're done with work for today

117
00:05:59,167 --> 00:06:00,433
and everyone did a great job.

118
00:06:01,167 --> 00:06:02,033
I think

119
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:03,300
you really should take a break

120
00:06:03,300 --> 00:06:04,667
and unwind.

121
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,300
Yifan

122
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:13,833
I feel like you're bottling up a lot.

123
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:18,933
You should try

124
00:06:19,467 --> 00:06:20,800
to open up a little

125
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:23,500
let go of any negative emotions

126
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:25,633
or unhappy thoughts

127
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,167
and welcome the new year

128
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,667
with a fresh mindset.

129
00:06:47,567 --> 00:06:48,600
The new year

130
00:06:49,167 --> 00:06:50,133
will be good, right?

131
00:06:52,033 --> 00:06:54,067
Happy New Year!

132
00:07:27,933 --> 00:07:28,933
The new year

133
00:07:30,233 --> 00:07:31,033
will be good, right?

134
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:34,567
Whether it's good or not

135
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:36,633
is entirely up to you.

136
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:45,733
[My New Year's wish]

137
00:07:45,733 --> 00:07:50,333
[My New Year's wish: A peaceful and uneventful year]

138
00:07:52,667 --> 00:07:57,100
笙ｪOnce again, I hear the farewell from that day笙ｪ

139
00:07:59,467 --> 00:08:04,333
笙ｪTears fall as the memory replays笙ｪ

140
00:08:06,367 --> 00:08:11,533
笙ｪLetting go of the past I once held tight笙ｪ

141
00:08:12,567 --> 00:08:14,267
笙ｪWishing for笙ｪ

142
00:08:14,533 --> 00:08:17,133
笙ｪA better chapter ahead笙ｪ

143
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,667
Somebody just fell.

144
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:22,300
Are you okay?

145
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,033
Let me help you up.

146
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:27,300
Sorry.

147
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:28,300
You are...

148
00:08:29,167 --> 00:08:29,933
Su...

149
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:31,300
- Haoan. - Yifan.

150
00:08:33,367 --> 00:08:34,667
I'm not Wen Yifan

151
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:35,667
I'm Zhong Siqiao.

152
00:08:35,667 --> 00:08:37,000
How could you mix that up?

153
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:37,867
Oh, that's right.

154
00:08:37,867 --> 00:08:39,500
I meant you're Wen Yifan's friend

155
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,800
Zhong Siqiao from the class next door.

156
00:08:53,967 --> 00:08:54,633
You are here.

157
00:08:55,900 --> 00:08:56,467
Who's that?

158
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,233
He's my other business partner.

159
00:08:58,867 --> 00:09:00,167
You probably remember him.

160
00:09:00,433 --> 00:09:02,033
He was my classmate in high school.

161
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,467
Headliner?

162
00:09:30,733 --> 00:09:31,567
Dian

163
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,033
do you know who the Headliner of Gastropub Street is?

164
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,733
It's Sang Yan.

165
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,033
Did you not recognize him, or were you just not telling me?

166
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:48,233
[Sang Yan. Happy New Year! You don't have to be happy.]

167
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:55,700
笙ｪFrom my heart to my whole being笙ｪ

168
00:09:57,700 --> 00:10:02,667
笙ｪFrom the sights before me to the vast world笙ｪ

169
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:13,833
笙ｪFor a fleeting moment, I fall in love with this world笙ｪ

170
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:19,167
笙ｪBut a world like this exists only tonight笙ｪ

171
00:10:22,533 --> 00:10:27,300
笙ｪFor a fleeting moment, I make peace with myself笙ｪ

172
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:32,967
笙ｪBut this version of me exists only tonight笙ｪ

173
00:10:37,133 --> 00:10:40,767
笙ｪOnly tonight笙ｪ

174
00:10:44,033 --> 00:10:48,267
笙ｪOnly tonight笙ｪ

175
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:55,767
笙ｪUntil I find the courage to be kind to myself笙ｪ

176
00:10:57,567 --> 00:11:01,467
笙ｪOnly tonight笙ｪ

177
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:09,700
笙ｪI almost believe I can hold onto tomorrow笙ｪ

178
00:11:13,267 --> 00:11:17,167
笙ｪOnly tonight笙ｪ

179
00:11:31,033 --> 00:11:33,267
[Uptown Flower City]

180
00:11:33,733 --> 00:11:34,633
Come in and feel free to look around.

181
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:37,500
This is one of the rooms.

182
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:39,667
Mine is the one at the far end.

183
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:42,867
I saw Su Tian mention in the group chat that you're looking for a place.

184
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,433
It's hard to find a place at the moment, isn't it?

185
00:11:45,333 --> 00:11:47,200
It's indeed hard to find a place during the Chinese New Year period.

186
00:11:47,267 --> 00:11:48,400
It's even harder to find a place

187
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,900
as close to the company

188
00:11:50,067 --> 00:11:51,133
as mine.

189
00:11:51,633 --> 00:11:52,567
You can thank me later.

190
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:55,333
Distance isn't a big concern for me.

191
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:56,333
What I'd like to know is the rent.

192
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:57,867
How can you not care about distance?

193
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,200
In our line of work

194
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:01,200
we're always on the go, working crazy hours.

195
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,833
Time is money.

196
00:12:02,833 --> 00:12:04,467
If you can sleep longer, why wake up earlier?

197
00:12:08,233 --> 00:12:09,433
This room is yours if you want it.

198
00:12:09,767 --> 00:12:11,067
The last tenant was a friend of mine

199
00:12:11,167 --> 00:12:12,400
who had moved out for a while.

200
00:12:12,633 --> 00:12:13,967
She dated a rich guy

201
00:12:13,967 --> 00:12:15,033
and upgraded to a hillside villa.

202
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:16,833
Here's the bathroom.

203
00:12:18,567 --> 00:12:20,067
Honestly, renting with strangers

204
00:12:20,067 --> 00:12:21,733
these days is too risky.

205
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:24,867
There are too many weirdos out there.

206
00:12:25,067 --> 00:12:26,400
That's why I'd rather leave it vacant

207
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,000
than rent it to someone I don't know.

208
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:29,367
That's why

209
00:12:29,367 --> 00:12:30,733
I offered it to you first.

210
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:32,667
Take a look before you decide.

211
00:12:32,667 --> 00:12:33,667
Moving isn't a small thing

212
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:34,833
after all.

213
00:12:39,433 --> 00:12:40,800
So, that vacant room of yours...

214
00:12:44,167 --> 00:12:44,967
I need to take this call.

215
00:12:45,567 --> 00:12:46,400
Help yourself to some water.

216
00:12:49,233 --> 00:12:49,867
Hey.

217
00:12:51,033 --> 00:12:52,500
I just wanted to ask

218
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,000
if you got the New Year's photos.

219
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:57,133
I mean the ones from our hot spring trip.

220
00:12:59,900 --> 00:13:01,233
Don't show them to anyone else.

221
00:13:02,733 --> 00:13:03,867
Don't call me that.

222
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,067
I'm not your girlfriend.

223
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:06,000
I'm hanging up.

224
00:13:10,767 --> 00:13:11,333
So, what do you think?

225
00:13:11,967 --> 00:13:13,967
The smaller room is 3

226
00:13:16,467 --> 00:13:17,567
We can split

227
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:18,800
the utility bills equally.

228
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:25,800
But if you're planning

229
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:28,367
on running the AC all day

230
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:29,833
taking super long showers

231
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:32,333
and cooking daily

232
00:13:32,767 --> 00:13:34,267
then we'll need a different arrangement.

233
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:39,500
I'll take it then.

234
00:13:42,267 --> 00:13:43,200
Welcome to your new home

235
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:44,167
at Uptown Flower City.

236
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:47,867
Let me know

237
00:13:48,133 --> 00:13:48,967
if you need anything.

238
00:14:06,967 --> 00:14:09,600
Although the rent here is much higher than in Urban Haven

239
00:14:10,067 --> 00:14:12,200
as long as I can get a good night's sleep

240
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:13,467
it's fine.

241
00:14:17,133 --> 00:14:17,800
Lin

242
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,900
you've already broken up with your ex.

243
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,033
Why are you still having a meal with him?

244
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,367
He kept begging me

245
00:14:22,367 --> 00:14:23,767
to give him another chance.

246
00:14:24,167 --> 00:14:26,067
I know we're done

247
00:14:26,167 --> 00:14:27,567
but having a meal together doesn't hurt.

248
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:29,867
He even booked a fancy restaurant

249
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:31,233
so don't hesitate to dig in.

250
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:33,800
Lin.

251
00:14:34,567 --> 00:14:35,400
Get in the car.

252
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:36,433
I wasn't late.

253
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,733
I actually arrived half an hour ago.

254
00:14:37,967 --> 00:14:39,333
I just wanted to buy you a flower.

255
00:14:42,333 --> 00:14:42,967
Wen Yifan?

256
00:14:46,767 --> 00:14:47,600
You're Wen Yifan, aren't you?

257
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:48,867
I'm not mistaken this time, am I?

258
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:51,467
Are you Su Haoan?

259
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:52,333
Yes, it's me.

260
00:14:52,767 --> 00:14:54,733
I ran into Zhong Siqiao at Overtime last night

261
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:55,833
and even mistook her for you.

262
00:14:58,667 --> 00:14:59,433
Let's talk in the car.

263
00:15:02,967 --> 00:15:04,333
Maybe it's better if I don't go.

264
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:05,000
Why?

265
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:06,733
It's fine.

266
00:15:06,867 --> 00:15:08,067
Let's celebrate becoming roommates.

267
00:15:09,433 --> 00:15:10,000
Careful.

268
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:11,700
OK.

269
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:13,467
Careful.

270
00:15:14,033 --> 00:15:14,633
Sit tight.

271
00:15:17,233 --> 00:15:18,200
There's someone else.

272
00:15:28,167 --> 00:15:29,333
Wake up and see your romantic interest.

273
00:15:29,567 --> 00:15:30,400
Wen Yifan is here.

274
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:35,800
So, you all know each other?

275
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,567
We were in the same class in high school.

276
00:15:39,167 --> 00:15:40,367
Romantic interest?

277
00:15:40,633 --> 00:15:41,600
What does that mean?

278
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,333
Are you saying Sang Yan had feelings for Fan

279
00:15:43,333 --> 00:15:44,033
but she never reciprocated?

280
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:46,033
Yes.

281
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:47,767
Really? How come I don't remember?

282
00:15:48,400 --> 00:15:49,567
Maybe you misremembered.

283
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:51,600
There's no way I misremembered.

284
00:15:51,633 --> 00:15:53,367
Back in high school, weren't you two...?

285
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:01,867
Is this awkward for you guys?

286
00:16:02,867 --> 00:16:04,167
It's been so many years.

287
00:16:04,167 --> 00:16:06,267
I was just bringing it up as a fun memory.

288
00:16:06,833 --> 00:16:08,733
How long has it been since you last saw each other?

289
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:10,900
Wen Yifan, I recall

290
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:13,133
you transferred schools in either your first or second year of high school.

291
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:16,233
The second semester of sophomore year.

292
00:16:17,367 --> 00:16:18,500
So

293
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:19,900
it's been seven or eight years now.

294
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:21,600
Sang Yan

295
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,433
why aren't you saying anything?

296
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:25,333
Don't tell me you're still

297
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:26,433
holding a grudge over this.

298
00:16:27,367 --> 00:16:28,500
He probably thinks

299
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,733
Wen Yifan had poor taste back then

300
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:30,400
and didn't fancy him.

301
00:16:30,400 --> 00:16:32,167
Who knew he'd turn out just like this?

302
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:33,000
Stop it.

303
00:16:33,233 --> 00:16:34,233
Just focus on driving.

304
00:16:41,267 --> 00:16:42,600
It's so late.

305
00:16:42,800 --> 00:16:44,200
Why are you taking so long?

306
00:16:44,333 --> 00:16:46,233
Do I have to come pick you up myself?

307
00:16:46,233 --> 00:16:47,067
We were stuck in traffic.

308
00:16:47,067 --> 00:16:48,667
Finally, you're here.

309
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:50,667
Who's that girl?

310
00:16:52,267 --> 00:16:53,567
Sang Yan, that's not cool.

311
00:16:53,967 --> 00:16:55,400
You got a girlfriend and didn't even tell us.

312
00:16:56,133 --> 00:16:56,867
Quit joking around.

313
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:57,967
She

314
00:16:58,067 --> 00:16:59,133
is our former classmate

315
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:01,167
the legendary beauty from our high school days.

316
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,233
No way Sang Yan could ever be in her league.

317
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:07,233
Wen Yifan

318
00:17:07,567 --> 00:17:08,467
meet

319
00:17:08,767 --> 00:17:09,933
Qian Fei and Chen Junwen.

320
00:17:09,933 --> 00:17:10,500
They

321
00:17:10,667 --> 00:17:11,933
were Sang Yan's dormmates.

322
00:17:11,933 --> 00:17:12,467
Hello.

323
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,000
As for me

324
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:14,367
I'm their closest friend.

325
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:18,933
The four of us run Overtime, our gastropub, together.

326
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:20,500
Hi.

327
00:17:21,067 --> 00:17:21,867
Don't try to cozy up to her.

328
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,833
Let's eat first. I'm starving.

329
00:17:26,167 --> 00:17:27,200
Let's eat. Come on.

330
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:32,633
Thank you.

331
00:17:39,933 --> 00:17:40,467
Come on.

332
00:17:42,467 --> 00:17:43,400
Let's have some cold dishes first.

333
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,433
We can treat today like a New Year's celebration.

334
00:17:45,733 --> 00:17:46,833
- Okay. - None of you

335
00:17:46,833 --> 00:17:47,767
were available on New Year's

336
00:17:47,767 --> 00:17:49,200
so I had to run Overtime all by myself.

337
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:50,767
I was working overtime.

338
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:52,133
It's part of my job.

339
00:17:52,133 --> 00:17:53,067
Just ask Fan if you don't believe me.

340
00:17:53,167 --> 00:17:54,733
I just wanted to ask

341
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:56,367
if you got the New Year's photos.

342
00:17:56,933 --> 00:17:58,933
I mean the ones from our hot spring trip.

343
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:02,567
It's okay

344
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:03,867
as long as you're here.

345
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:06,733
This is for you.

346
00:18:08,033 --> 00:18:08,767
Thanks.

347
00:18:15,100 --> 00:18:15,933
Since everyone's gathered here today

348
00:18:16,467 --> 00:18:18,300
let's celebrate Sang Yan's birthday together.

349
00:18:18,867 --> 00:18:19,567
January 2nd.

350
00:18:19,633 --> 00:18:20,400
A Capricorn?

351
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:21,567
I'm getting emotional.

352
00:18:21,933 --> 00:18:23,067
Did you get my permission

353
00:18:23,067 --> 00:18:24,000
to celebrate my birthday?

354
00:18:24,233 --> 00:18:25,500
Dude, this is a surprise.

355
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:26,400
Why aren't you showing some appreciation?

356
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,000
Dude

357
00:18:27,033 --> 00:18:27,800
you brought it up so early.

358
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:29,100
How can we still call this a surprise?

359
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:30,600
You know Su Haoan.

360
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:32,000
He can't keep secrets.

361
00:18:32,233 --> 00:18:33,100
You are quite something.

362
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:34,267
I'm speechless.

363
00:18:34,267 --> 00:18:35,000
Sorry.

364
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:35,667
My bad.

365
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:36,600
Come on.

366
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:38,267
Happy Birthday.

367
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:46,433
Fan

368
00:18:46,767 --> 00:18:47,967
you rejected

369
00:18:48,400 --> 00:18:49,467
Sang Yan before?

370
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:51,967
I just don't get it.

371
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,567
He's got everything

372
00:18:53,800 --> 00:18:55,733
the looks, the height, the money.

373
00:18:56,233 --> 00:18:57,033
But

374
00:18:57,467 --> 00:18:59,233
seeing how cold he is today

375
00:18:59,933 --> 00:19:02,000
it's possible he doesn't have any feelings for you anymore.

376
00:19:04,767 --> 00:19:05,567
It's all in the past now.

377
00:19:09,867 --> 00:19:10,800
You

378
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,567
need to learn how to seize opportunities.

379
00:19:12,967 --> 00:19:13,867
Sometimes

380
00:19:13,967 --> 00:19:15,500
finding a good partner

381
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,000
can be more effective than a promotion.

382
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:22,633
By the way, what lipstick shade are you wearing?

383
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:24,167
It's really nice.

384
00:19:24,467 --> 00:19:25,500
I didn't wear any today.

385
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:26,467
Normally I use...

386
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:28,867
We are both women.

387
00:19:28,867 --> 00:19:30,300
Can't you just be honest?

388
00:19:37,000 --> 00:19:38,100
I really didn't wear any.

389
00:19:56,167 --> 00:19:57,267
It's been a while.

390
00:20:00,867 --> 00:20:03,000
It's been a while?

391
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:06,033
It's only been two days since the New Year's event.

392
00:20:06,567 --> 00:20:07,467
No need to act

393
00:20:07,733 --> 00:20:09,367
like you've been missing me as if it's been ages.

394
00:20:12,933 --> 00:20:14,933
You were the one acting like you didn't know me.

395
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:17,733
I thought you didn't recognize me

396
00:20:17,733 --> 00:20:19,100
since I was wearing a mask that day

397
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:20,400
covering my face completely.

398
00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:22,200
I didn't expect your eyes to be that sharp.

399
00:20:22,767 --> 00:20:23,933
My eyes are sharp?

400
00:20:26,033 --> 00:20:26,600
Sorry

401
00:20:27,367 --> 00:20:27,933
you got it wrong.

402
00:20:29,067 --> 00:20:30,000
I didn't see you at all.

403
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:31,733
It was my sister who saw you

404
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:33,433
and mentioned

405
00:20:33,667 --> 00:20:35,000
that you were staring at me.

406
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:38,700
That's true.

407
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:39,867
Because I noticed

408
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,233
your zipper was down.

409
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:48,767
A lot of people around me

410
00:20:48,767 --> 00:20:50,033
were talking about it at the time.

411
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:52,433
But don't worry too much

412
00:20:52,433 --> 00:20:53,033
since it has been

413
00:20:53,933 --> 00:20:55,200
a few hours already.

414
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:55,867
I'm off now.

415
00:21:20,233 --> 00:21:21,733
They were talking about a limited edition or something.

416
00:21:21,733 --> 00:21:22,267
Come on.

417
00:21:22,267 --> 00:21:23,467
Here, let's have a toast together.

418
00:21:24,367 --> 00:21:24,867
Here.

419
00:21:32,600 --> 00:21:34,100
Any updates on the singer?

420
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:35,133
A couple of friends

421
00:21:35,133 --> 00:21:36,133
recommended a few to me the other day.

422
00:21:36,133 --> 00:21:38,167
Sorry, I need to head back now.

423
00:21:38,767 --> 00:21:40,433
My supervisor just told me

424
00:21:40,800 --> 00:21:41,867
that I have a task to finish.

425
00:21:42,033 --> 00:21:43,133
You hardly ate anything.

426
00:21:43,133 --> 00:21:43,733
Are you full?

427
00:21:43,733 --> 00:21:44,633
Is it because of Ms. Qian?

428
00:21:44,633 --> 00:21:45,367
I'll talk to her.

429
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,700
No need. I just passed my probation period

430
00:21:46,700 --> 00:21:47,267
if you know what I mean.

431
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:48,933
You've worked hard.

432
00:21:49,067 --> 00:21:49,967
Stay safe on your way back.

433
00:21:49,967 --> 00:21:50,500
Okay.

434
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:51,433
Bye.

435
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:54,467
What's wrong?

436
00:21:56,367 --> 00:21:57,000
Let's have a toast together.

437
00:22:16,933 --> 00:22:18,433
Do you still remember which floor Su Haoan's car

438
00:22:18,433 --> 00:22:19,067
was parked on?

439
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:21,033
I think it's on the second basement floor.

440
00:22:21,033 --> 00:22:22,233
You don't remember?

441
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,300
Which section and what number?

442
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,233
It should be section A

443
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:30,033
at the turn.

444
00:22:31,100 --> 00:22:32,267
All right, lead the way.

445
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:45,267
Here it is.

446
00:22:54,233 --> 00:22:54,833
Hey

447
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:58,467
could you give me a ride?

448
00:22:58,667 --> 00:23:00,300
It's really hard to get a cab during rush hour.

449
00:23:00,300 --> 00:23:00,867
Where do you live?

450
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:01,967
Urban Haven.

451
00:23:03,433 --> 00:23:04,033
It's a detour for me.

452
00:23:05,167 --> 00:23:06,400
I won't trouble you then.

453
00:23:27,633 --> 00:23:29,567
[56 people ahead, estimated waiting time is 60 minutes]

454
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,267
I never said I wouldn't give you a ride just because it's a detour.

455
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,800
It's probably going to take over 50 minutes for you to get a cab now.

456
00:23:57,567 --> 00:23:59,367
[55 people ahead, estimated waiting time is 58 minutes]

457
00:23:59,667 --> 00:24:00,567
How come he knows?

458
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:02,067
Let's go.

459
00:24:08,967 --> 00:24:09,867
[54 people ahead, estimated waiting time is 57 minutes]

460
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:12,167
Thank you.

461
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:15,567
Um, you

462
00:24:15,967 --> 00:24:18,067
can just drop me off at the nearest subway station.

463
00:24:18,367 --> 00:24:19,167
Thanks for helping me out.

464
00:24:19,633 --> 00:24:21,167
Such good manners.

465
00:24:40,967 --> 00:24:42,100
How about some music?

466
00:24:48,367 --> 00:24:49,967
[Media]

467
00:24:49,967 --> 00:24:51,900
[China National Radio]

468
00:25:01,033 --> 00:25:02,833
Are you not staying to eat with them?

469
00:25:02,933 --> 00:25:03,733
They are too noisy.

470
00:25:05,567 --> 00:25:11,067
笙ｪJot down the wishes you've made before笙ｪ

471
00:25:11,167 --> 00:25:12,967
You haven't seen them in a while, right?

472
00:25:13,267 --> 00:25:13,867
Not really.

473
00:25:18,300 --> 00:25:19,633
It's your birthday today, right?

474
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:22,567
You forgot?

475
00:25:27,267 --> 00:25:32,833
笙ｪMy dear, don't say goodbye笙ｪ

476
00:25:37,833 --> 00:25:38,500
Do you like it?

477
00:25:40,633 --> 00:25:41,467
From you?

478
00:25:44,400 --> 00:25:45,933
What's with the sudden gift?

479
00:25:45,933 --> 00:25:46,667
It's for your birthday.

480
00:25:47,267 --> 00:25:48,433
I thought you were born

481
00:25:48,433 --> 00:25:49,500
during Frost's Descent.

482
00:25:51,467 --> 00:25:52,367
You remembered?

483
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:53,300
It's easy to remember.

484
00:25:56,433 --> 00:25:57,100
Thank you.

485
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:02,667
Does this mean

486
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:04,767
I'll have to remember

487
00:26:04,767 --> 00:26:05,933
your birthday from now on?

488
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,167
Don't worry about it.

489
00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:10,800
I don't really celebrate my birthday.

490
00:26:10,967 --> 00:26:14,267
笙ｪWarm up your palms笙ｪ

491
00:26:16,267 --> 00:26:17,867
I'm a Capricorn, born on January 2nd

492
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:19,633
and I'm not really into celebrating my birthday.

493
00:26:21,567 --> 00:26:28,167
笙ｪFrom now on, when you're lost, don't forget the one beside you笙ｪ

494
00:26:28,933 --> 00:26:33,967
笙ｪSomeone's there to protect your pride笙ｪ

495
00:26:37,400 --> 00:26:38,733
We seem to have passed it.

496
00:26:41,367 --> 00:26:42,267
But it's all right.

497
00:26:42,667 --> 00:26:44,433
There's another subway entrance ahead

498
00:26:44,433 --> 00:26:45,600
just drop me off there.

499
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:46,433
Am I your driver?

500
00:26:52,433 --> 00:26:54,233
Where are we going then?

501
00:26:54,433 --> 00:26:55,233
Your home, of course.

502
00:26:55,467 --> 00:26:56,433
Where else do you think we'll be going?

503
00:26:57,833 --> 00:26:59,700
笙ｪThis time笙ｪ

504
00:27:09,067 --> 00:27:09,933
So

505
00:27:10,667 --> 00:27:12,100
when you are free next time

506
00:27:12,100 --> 00:27:13,433
I'll treat you to a meal.

507
00:27:13,467 --> 00:27:14,800
Thanks a lot for today.

508
00:27:15,367 --> 00:27:17,167
You're already planning for our next meeting?

509
00:27:22,500 --> 00:27:23,933
Earlier at Overtime

510
00:27:24,833 --> 00:27:26,300
I think I misspoke.

511
00:27:27,067 --> 00:27:27,767
What are you referring to?

512
00:27:29,300 --> 00:27:30,733
You mean when you said it was a bit of a pity?

513
00:27:34,233 --> 00:27:35,733
Thank you. I'll go home now.

514
00:27:38,233 --> 00:27:41,467
笙ｪFate changes and the confessions come too late笙ｪ

515
00:27:41,933 --> 00:27:44,633
笙ｪThe love that was once absent笙ｪ

516
00:27:45,733 --> 00:27:55,900
笙ｪHolding you close, never letting go again笙ｪ

517
00:28:37,767 --> 00:28:38,567
Dian.

518
00:28:42,267 --> 00:28:43,033
Dian.

519
00:28:46,067 --> 00:28:47,533
Hey, does it taste all right to you?

520
00:28:47,533 --> 00:28:48,033
It's not bad.

521
00:28:52,267 --> 00:28:53,033
Eat more.

522
00:28:58,767 --> 00:28:59,500
Who is it?

523
00:29:01,600 --> 00:29:02,733
Oh, the pretty lady.

524
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:03,800
You are back.

525
00:29:04,933 --> 00:29:06,067
Give me back my cat.

526
00:29:07,067 --> 00:29:08,567
We've finally met in person.

527
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:10,433
So you're the one who had our friends stuck

528
00:29:10,833 --> 00:29:12,167
at the police station for days, huh?

529
00:29:25,933 --> 00:29:28,167
You don't know how to maintain harmony with the neighbors, do you?

530
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:29,633
Give me back my cat.

531
00:29:29,767 --> 00:29:30,433
Here.

532
00:29:30,433 --> 00:29:31,100
Here's your cat.

533
00:29:32,633 --> 00:29:34,033
I think she really doesn't get it.

534
00:29:34,100 --> 00:29:35,967
Should we teach her a lesson?

535
00:29:36,567 --> 00:29:37,667
- Go away! - Don't be afraid.

536
00:29:37,667 --> 00:29:38,467
Let go of me!

537
00:29:39,167 --> 00:29:39,967
Go away!

538
00:29:40,967 --> 00:29:41,667
My foot.

539
00:29:44,367 --> 00:29:44,933
Go after her!

540
00:29:45,733 --> 00:29:46,267
Stop right there!

541
00:29:49,300 --> 00:29:50,133
Stop!

542
00:29:52,033 --> 00:29:52,667
Stop right there!

543
00:29:59,267 --> 00:29:59,767
Stop!

544
00:30:01,033 --> 00:30:01,633
Are you all right?

545
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:02,600
Stop!

546
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:06,300
- Go after her! - Stop!

547
00:30:07,067 --> 00:30:07,600
Go after her!

548
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:10,400
Keep running.

549
00:30:10,933 --> 00:30:12,200
You were pretty fast, weren't you?

550
00:30:13,733 --> 00:30:15,000
Keep running then.

551
00:30:16,733 --> 00:30:17,300
Darn it!

552
00:30:18,367 --> 00:30:18,867
Who did this?

553
00:30:21,633 --> 00:30:22,233
Give me your hand.

554
00:30:23,233 --> 00:30:23,733
Your hand.

555
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:25,433
Don't you dare to run away!

556
00:30:31,967 --> 00:30:32,467
Get in the car.

557
00:30:32,500 --> 00:30:33,200
What about you?

558
00:30:36,033 --> 00:30:36,833
Watch out!

559
00:30:46,167 --> 00:30:47,233
Watch out, Sang Yan.

560
00:30:52,833 --> 00:30:53,500
Open the door!

561
00:31:00,400 --> 00:31:00,967
Open the door!

562
00:31:04,767 --> 00:31:05,833
Watch out, Sang Yan.

563
00:31:06,933 --> 00:31:07,467
Stop!

564
00:31:12,467 --> 00:31:13,167
Is this the police?

565
00:31:13,433 --> 00:31:14,100
I need to file a report.

566
00:31:36,233 --> 00:31:36,967
Open the window.

567
00:31:40,667 --> 00:31:41,300
Careful.

568
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:42,200
All you all right?

569
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:42,867
Drive.

570
00:32:12,233 --> 00:32:13,800
Should we head to the hospital?

571
00:32:18,200 --> 00:32:19,833
Do you have any other injuries?

572
00:32:20,300 --> 00:32:21,633
- Let's go to the hospital. - Wen Yifan.

573
00:32:25,733 --> 00:32:26,933
Did you not see me standing there?

574
00:32:30,300 --> 00:32:31,033
What's the matter?

575
00:32:31,033 --> 00:32:31,833
Why didn't you ask me for help?

576
00:32:31,833 --> 00:32:32,733
Why did you run?

577
00:32:38,433 --> 00:32:39,400
Where did you go?

578
00:32:39,400 --> 00:32:40,833
Why is it taking you so long to grab something?

579
00:32:41,433 --> 00:32:42,933
I'm still waiting for you to come back and cut the cake.

580
00:32:43,167 --> 00:32:44,033
- Stop nagging. - Stop!

581
00:32:44,033 --> 00:32:44,767
I'll be right back.

582
00:32:49,433 --> 00:32:50,033
Stop!

583
00:32:51,067 --> 00:32:51,867
Wen Yifan.

584
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:54,500
Come here.

585
00:32:56,167 --> 00:32:56,800
Stop!

586
00:33:00,667 --> 00:33:02,233
I was so loud when I told you to come over. Couldn't you hear me?

587
00:33:02,633 --> 00:33:03,633
You could neither hear me nor see me.

588
00:33:03,633 --> 00:33:05,167
You were too busy racing against others, huh?

589
00:33:17,867 --> 00:33:19,933
Actually, I wanted to ask you for help

590
00:33:20,967 --> 00:33:21,733
but I wasn't sure

591
00:33:21,967 --> 00:33:23,600
if they'd actually get physical.

592
00:33:28,833 --> 00:33:30,033
I didn't want to drag you into it

593
00:33:33,667 --> 00:33:34,200
Besides

594
00:33:35,033 --> 00:33:37,000
there are three of them.

595
00:33:37,300 --> 00:33:38,000
I

596
00:33:38,567 --> 00:33:39,633
was worried you might not be able to handle them.

597
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,233
Is it okay if I pull over up ahead?

598
00:33:58,767 --> 00:34:02,067
[Heping Pharmacy]

599
00:34:03,867 --> 00:34:04,600
Wait for me.

600
00:34:21,167 --> 00:34:21,967
Welcome to our store.

601
00:34:48,833 --> 00:34:49,400
What are you doing?

602
00:34:49,700 --> 00:34:50,600
Apply some ointment.

603
00:34:52,267 --> 00:34:52,867
No, thanks.

604
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:56,300
If you don't apply the ointment

605
00:34:56,300 --> 00:34:57,933
I'm worried you might get tetanus

606
00:34:59,033 --> 00:35:00,400
and it could be fatal.

607
00:35:01,333 --> 00:35:02,433
I don't want

608
00:35:02,433 --> 00:35:03,800
to be responsible for that.

609
00:35:30,233 --> 00:35:31,267
Do you need a hand?

610
00:35:53,233 --> 00:35:53,833
Does it hurt?

611
00:35:54,967 --> 00:35:55,667
No.

612
00:36:14,433 --> 00:36:15,667
Let me apply some on your face as well.

613
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:25,000
You are just applying some ointment.

614
00:36:25,367 --> 00:36:26,767
Is it necessary to get so close?

615
00:36:29,267 --> 00:36:30,067
Sorry.

616
00:36:31,667 --> 00:36:33,700
It's too dark, and I'm worried that I can't see clearly.

617
00:36:47,167 --> 00:36:47,967
All right.

618
00:36:48,200 --> 00:36:48,933
Turn around.

619
00:36:55,033 --> 00:36:57,167
笙ｪLook at me笙ｪ

620
00:36:58,167 --> 00:37:00,767
笙ｪI want you to look at me笙ｪ

621
00:37:02,300 --> 00:37:04,933
笙ｪJust keep looking at me笙ｪ

622
00:37:06,500 --> 00:37:10,300
笙ｪBorrow the light from the stars and the moon to gaze at me笙ｪ

623
00:37:10,833 --> 00:37:13,033
笙ｪIt's not me笙ｪ

624
00:37:14,333 --> 00:37:16,533
笙ｪI know it's not me笙ｪ

625
00:37:16,567 --> 00:37:17,367
I'll do it myself.

626
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:21,133
笙ｪBut I can't help but feel it's a pity笙ｪ

627
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:23,433
笙ｪBecause I lack the courage笙ｪ

628
00:37:23,500 --> 00:37:26,367
笙ｪI've never said it to you笙ｪ

629
00:37:26,700 --> 00:37:30,533
笙ｪI want to say that I love you笙ｪ

630
00:37:30,700 --> 00:37:33,833
笙ｪHow do I tell you that I love you?笙ｪ

631
00:37:34,700 --> 00:37:38,500
笙ｪI always wish my eyes could speak for me笙ｪ

632
00:37:38,567 --> 00:37:42,500
笙ｪI've imagined countless times you saying yes to me笙ｪ

633
00:37:44,633 --> 00:37:45,333
Where will you be staying tonight?

634
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:47,867
I'll stay

635
00:37:47,867 --> 00:37:49,833
at my friend's place tonight.

636
00:37:50,167 --> 00:37:51,933
But I've already found a new place.

637
00:37:52,033 --> 00:37:53,400
I just haven't had the time to move yet.

638
00:37:58,267 --> 00:37:58,933
Goodbye.

639
00:38:01,833 --> 00:38:03,500
笙ｪWithout you笙ｪ

640
00:38:15,033 --> 00:38:17,167
笙ｪIt's not me笙ｪ

641
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:20,767
笙ｪI know it's not me笙ｪ

642
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:25,333
笙ｪBut I can't help but feel it's a pity笙ｪ

643
00:38:25,633 --> 00:38:27,567
笙ｪBecause I lack the courage笙ｪ

644
00:38:27,867 --> 00:38:30,533
笙ｪI've never said it to you笙ｪ

645
00:38:30,967 --> 00:38:34,733
笙ｪI want to say that I love you笙ｪ

646
00:38:35,067 --> 00:38:38,067
笙ｪHow do I tell you that I love you?笙ｪ

647
00:38:38,933 --> 00:38:42,633
笙ｪI always wish my eyes could speak for me笙ｪ

648
00:38:42,933 --> 00:38:46,633
笙ｪI've imagined countless times you saying yes to me笙ｪ

649
00:38:46,933 --> 00:38:50,700
笙ｪI want to say that I love you笙ｪ

650
00:38:51,133 --> 00:38:54,567
笙ｪI forgot to tell you I love you笙ｪ

651
00:38:55,167 --> 00:38:58,567
笙ｪThe distance drains all the oxygen from me笙ｪ

652
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:02,867
笙ｪMaking me suffocate in the mornings笙ｪ

653
00:39:06,733 --> 00:39:08,500
笙ｪWithout you笙ｪ

654
00:39:19,100 --> 00:39:19,967
This is my place.

655
00:39:24,033 --> 00:39:24,833
Goodbye.

656
00:39:25,167 --> 00:39:27,033
Are you going to keep saying goodbye?

657
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:34,600
Is there anything else?

658
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:35,600
Go in and pack your things.

659
00:39:37,667 --> 00:39:39,333
You're not actually planning to come back to this dump, are you?

660
00:39:54,500 --> 00:39:55,567
Feel free to sit down.

661
00:39:55,567 --> 00:39:56,800
I'll go pack my things.

662
00:39:57,233 --> 00:39:57,967
No, thanks.

663
00:40:04,067 --> 00:40:05,233
I bet you were terrified just now.

664
00:40:35,033 --> 00:40:35,600
Let me ask you this.

665
00:40:36,767 --> 00:40:37,933
After all that has happened

666
00:40:38,333 --> 00:40:39,433
why haven't you been more careful?

667
00:40:41,800 --> 00:40:44,033
I thought that person was still at the police station

668
00:40:44,033 --> 00:40:45,267
so I assumed it was safe for the time being.

669
00:40:49,867 --> 00:40:50,800
Are these all you've got?

670
00:40:52,033 --> 00:40:53,033
I'm on my own.

671
00:40:53,567 --> 00:40:54,767
I don't have a lot of stuff.

672
00:40:55,233 --> 00:40:56,067
These are everything I own.

673
00:41:41,633 --> 00:41:42,367
We are almost there.

674
00:41:44,367 --> 00:41:45,500
Which building does your friend live in?

675
00:41:46,600 --> 00:41:48,367
I can't quite remember.

676
00:41:48,933 --> 00:41:50,467
I came during the day the last time.

677
00:41:52,967 --> 00:41:54,200
Do you really have a friend living here?

678
00:41:58,033 --> 00:42:00,600
I really appreciate your help today.

679
00:42:02,433 --> 00:42:03,700
Let me know when you're free

680
00:42:03,700 --> 00:42:04,833
and I'll treat you to a meal.

681
00:42:04,833 --> 00:42:05,800
Don't worry about the meal.

682
00:42:05,800 --> 00:42:07,467
Even if I didn't know you

683
00:42:08,067 --> 00:42:09,333
I would've done the same thing today.

684
00:42:12,600 --> 00:42:14,267
After all the heroic acts

685
00:42:14,933 --> 00:42:16,000
will your face still be presentable

686
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:18,633
by the end of the year?

687
00:42:22,933 --> 00:42:23,800
Even if

688
00:42:24,167 --> 00:42:25,933
you're temporarily scarred

689
00:42:26,500 --> 00:42:28,600
it doesn't take away your charm.

690
00:42:41,567 --> 00:42:42,267
Thanks.

691
00:42:42,400 --> 00:42:43,600
You can just put them here.

692
00:42:48,500 --> 00:42:50,100
I could have handled it on my own.

693
00:42:50,100 --> 00:42:51,367
[Uptown Flower City]

694
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:02,267
Thank you.

695
00:43:04,767 --> 00:43:05,600
You can just leave them here.

696
00:43:05,600 --> 00:43:07,033
My roommate is a girl.

697
00:43:07,033 --> 00:43:08,400
I can go up myself.

698
00:43:10,167 --> 00:43:10,800
I'm leaving now.

699
00:43:49,733 --> 00:43:51,233
[Episode 2]
[Your Name]

700
00:43:51,233 --> 00:43:51,833
[Wen Yifan]

701
00:43:51,833 --> 00:43:53,733
[Happy New Year! You don't have to be happy.]

702
00:43:53,733 --> 00:43:55,633
[Episode 2]
[Your Name Is Written on My Heart]

703
00:44:00,633 --> 00:44:01,233
Bro.

704
00:44:01,500 --> 00:44:02,700
[The story is not over yet...]
Congratulations on making it out.

705
00:44:02,700 --> 00:44:03,933
First, take a shower

706
00:44:03,933 --> 00:44:04,600
to wash off the bad luck

707
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:06,333
then step over a fire pot.

708
00:44:07,100 --> 00:44:07,767
Come on

709
00:44:07,800 --> 00:44:08,767
we will drink with you

710
00:44:08,767 --> 00:44:09,767
to your heart's content tonight.

711
00:44:09,967 --> 00:44:10,467
Here.

712
00:44:11,333 --> 00:44:12,633
My wife was gone

713
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:14,267
and on top of that, I ended up in the police station.

714
00:44:14,467 --> 00:44:15,000
Yeah.

715
00:44:15,100 --> 00:44:15,833
We intended

716
00:44:15,833 --> 00:44:17,600
to bring her to apologize to you a few days ago

717
00:44:17,600 --> 00:44:19,200
but unfortunately, she ran away.

718
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:20,733
Honestly

719
00:44:20,733 --> 00:44:22,267
I should have installed a camera

720
00:44:22,267 --> 00:44:23,500
and filmed it all from the beginning.

721
00:44:23,767 --> 00:44:25,067
She doesn't want me to see it, huh?

722
00:44:25,067 --> 00:44:26,867
- Yes. - I'll show it to the whole world.

723
00:44:27,233 --> 00:44:27,867
Exactly.

724
00:44:28,200 --> 00:44:29,767
- Let's drink. - Come on, bro.

725
00:44:30,233 --> 00:44:34,267
笙ｪI want to quietly slip into your soul笙ｪ

726
00:44:34,967 --> 00:44:38,667
笙ｪTo catch you every time you feel vulnerable笙ｪ

727
00:44:39,567 --> 00:44:42,367
笙ｪTo find you笙ｪ

728
00:44:43,567 --> 00:44:46,633
笙ｪTo protect you笙ｪ

729
00:44:49,967 --> 00:44:50,600
Wait

730
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:52,600
what's going on?

731
00:44:54,667 --> 00:44:56,000
I just wanted to check

732
00:44:58,267 --> 00:45:00,367
if they really installed hidden cameras.

733
00:45:00,933 --> 00:45:04,100
笙ｪTo protect you笙ｪ

734
00:45:04,100 --> 00:45:04,967
Hey, are you serious?

735
00:45:04,967 --> 00:45:06,900
Are you some kind of creep?

736
00:45:06,900 --> 00:45:07,967
Cameras? Are you kidding me?

737
00:45:08,967 --> 00:45:10,167
What's wrong with you?

738
00:45:10,567 --> 00:45:11,400
Did you all

739
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:13,233
see my floral boxer?

740
00:45:13,233 --> 00:45:14,867
- No, I just... - You want to sell it for cash, huh?

741
00:45:20,467 --> 00:45:21,767
笙ｪEven the strongest heart笙ｪ

742
00:45:21,933 --> 00:45:23,633
笙ｪCan waver笙ｪ

743
00:45:23,867 --> 00:45:27,067
笙ｪAnd doubt its fire笙ｪ

744
00:45:27,300 --> 00:45:28,933
笙ｪBut you never lost faith in me笙ｪ

745
00:45:28,933 --> 00:45:30,633
笙ｪIn every battle, every dream I chased笙ｪ

746
00:45:30,833 --> 00:45:33,500
笙ｪThere is meaning in every step I made笙ｪ

747
00:45:34,333 --> 00:45:40,300
笙ｪThrough the storm, through the endless night笙ｪ

748
00:45:40,667 --> 00:45:42,300
笙ｪYou were there, shining like a light笙ｪ

749
00:45:42,300 --> 00:45:43,967
笙ｪWarm and bright笙ｪ

750
00:45:44,133 --> 00:45:47,867
笙ｪStanding right by my side笙ｪ

751
00:45:48,300 --> 00:45:54,433
笙ｪIt was you, striding toward me through the storm笙ｪ

752
00:45:54,767 --> 00:46:01,700
笙ｪIt was you, always cheering me on笙ｪ

753
00:46:01,867 --> 00:46:04,867
笙ｪThe road is rough笙ｪ

754
00:46:05,167 --> 00:46:09,300
笙ｪThe rain won't stop笙ｪ

755
00:46:09,500 --> 00:46:13,467
笙ｪBut with you here笙ｪ

756
00:46:13,733 --> 00:46:19,767
笙ｪI fear no dark笙ｪ

757
00:46:23,033 --> 00:46:26,633
笙ｪEvery thought, every memory is filled with you笙ｪ

758
00:46:26,933 --> 00:46:30,433
笙ｪMarking our youth with every step we took笙ｪ

759
00:46:30,700 --> 00:46:32,567
笙ｪWhen the downpour falls from the sky笙ｪ

760
00:46:32,567 --> 00:46:36,233
笙ｪYou're the one holding out an umbrella for me笙ｪ

761
00:46:36,567 --> 00:46:40,133
笙ｪWhen the white dove brings the news笙ｪ

762
00:46:40,500 --> 00:46:43,933
笙ｪYou're the first I want to tell笙ｪ

763
00:46:44,333 --> 00:46:52,967
笙ｪI won't give up. I'll stay right here with you笙ｪ

764
00:46:57,567 --> 00:47:03,767
笙ｪIt was you, striding toward me through the storm笙ｪ

765
00:47:04,633 --> 00:47:11,067
笙ｪIt was you, always cheering me on笙ｪ

766
00:47:11,067 --> 00:47:14,233
笙ｪThe road is rough笙ｪ

767
00:47:14,700 --> 00:47:18,667
笙ｪThe rain won't stop笙ｪ

768
00:47:18,867 --> 00:47:21,500
笙ｪBut with you here笙ｪ

769
00:47:21,700 --> 00:47:25,533
笙ｪI will never give up笙ｪ

770
00:47:25,833 --> 00:47:31,900
笙ｪYou are my courage, my hope for the sky beyond笙ｪ

771
00:47:32,433 --> 00:47:38,267
笙ｪYou are my light, shining through every night笙ｪ

772
00:47:38,833 --> 00:47:41,667
笙ｪEven if I have to walk alone someday笙ｪ

773
00:47:42,100 --> 00:47:44,933
笙ｪI'll never truly be on my own笙ｪ

774
00:47:45,967 --> 00:47:50,500
笙ｪ'Cause knowing you're here笙ｪ

775
00:47:50,933 --> 00:47:57,533
笙ｪI can brave the dark ahead笙ｪ

776
00:47:59,367 --> 00:48:00,633
[Huge thanks to everyone involved and to all the fans of The First Frost!]
